title: Jaguars running back Yeldon won't play against Texans
text:
Jaguars rookie running back T.J. Yeldon won't play against Texans because of groin injury THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   11:36 amLast   11:36 am   
People: 
Texas (1310) 

JACKSONVILLE, Florida â€” The Jacksonville Jaguars will be without running back T.J. Yeldon against Houston on Sunday. 
The team ruled out Yeldon a few hours before kickoff, saying the rookie will miss the game because of a groin injury. Yeldon missed practice all week and had been listed as questionable. 
Yeldon has 291 yards rushing, 73 yards receiving and a touchdown this season. 
Without him, the Jaguars (1-4) are expected to use Denard Robinson and Toby Gerhart in the backfield. Robinson is returning after missing three games with a sprained left knee.
